{"abstract": "In \u201cThe Evolution of a Corporate Idealist,\u201d a former BP employee sees globalization and the Internet as pushing more companies to social responsibility.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/09/business/bookshelf-how-big-business-can-take-the-high-road.html", "snippet": "In \u201cThe Evolution of a Corporate Idealist,\u201d a former BP employee sees globalization and the Internet as pushing more companies to social responsibility.", "lead_paragraph": "It\u2019s been a long time \u2014 maybe never \u2014 since I\u2019ve read a book that made me feel proud or even a little encouraged about the moral compass of the world\u2019s largest companies. Corporations, after all, exist to make money. Last I checked, doing good deeds is not listed as a fiduciary duty. But Christine Bader\u2019s thought-provoking book, \u201cThe Evolution of a Corporate Idealist: When Girl Meets Oil\u201d (Bibliomotion, 264 pages), argues that this may be changing, at least among some of the people who work at these companies.", "print_section": "BU", "print_page": "10", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/09/business/9-SHELF/9-SHELF-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 891, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/03/09/business/9-SHELF/9-SHELF-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 891}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/09/business/9-SHELF/9-SHELF-jumbo.jpg", "height": 1024, "width": 690, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/09/business/9-SHELF/9-SHELF-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 2048, "width": 1380, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype